returns.fee: The amount of ETH accrued as fee

params._exemptedAmount: Amount in ETH to exempt from fee calculations

params._callData: The call data of the function.

returns._0: The confirmation expiration timestamp or 0 if there was no confirmation from this role to this _callData

returns.roles: is an array of roles that form the confirming roles.

params._lidoLocator: The address of the Lido locator.
params._vaultHub: The address of the vault hub.

returns._0: bool True if correction was applied, false if awaiting confirmations

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

getRoleMembers(bytes32).details: Return all accounts that have `role` WARNING: This operation will copy the entire storage to memory, which can be quite expensive. This is designed to mostly be used by view accessors that are queried without any gas fees. Developers should keep in mind that this function has an unbounded cost, and using it as part of a state-changing function may render the function uncallable if the set grows to a point where copying to memory consumes too much gas to fit in a block.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

grantRoles((address,bytes32)[]).details: Performs the role admin checks internally.If an account is already a member of a role, doesn't revert, emits no events.

returns._0: report The latest report containing totalValue, inOutDelta, and timestamp

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRoles((address,bytes32)[]).details: Performs the role admin checks internally.If an account is not a member of a role, doesn't revert, emits no events.

params._isApproved: True to approve, False to forbid

params._newConfirmExpiry: The new confirmation expiry period in seconds

returns._0: bool True if expiry was updated, false if awaiting confirmations

params._newFeeRate: The new fee rate in basis points (max 10000 = 100%)

returns._0: bool True if fee rate was updated, false if still awaiting confirmations

params._newFeeRecipient: The new recipient address for fee payments

NODE_OPERATOR_FEE_EXEMPT_ROLE().notice: Node operator's sub-role for fee exemptions. Managed by `NODE_OPERATOR_MANAGER_ROLE`.

NODE_OPERATOR_MANAGER_ROLE().notice: Parent role representing the node operator of the underlying StakingVault. The members may not include the node operator address recorded in the underlying StakingVault but it is assumed that the members of this role act in the interest of that node operator.

NODE_OPERATOR_PROVE_UNKNOWN_VALIDATOR_RO.notice: Node operator's sub-role for proving unknown validators. Managed by `NODE_OPERATOR_MANAGER_ROLE`.

NODE_OPERATOR_UNGUARANTEED_DEPOSIT_ROLE(.notice: Node operator's sub-role for unguaranteed deposit Managed by `NODE_OPERATOR_MANAGER_ROLE`.

accruedFee().notice: Calculates the current node operator fee amount in ETH. Fee calculation steps: 1. Retrieve latest vault report (totalValue, inOutDelta) 2. Calculate current growth: totalValue - inOutDelta 3. Determine unsettled growth: currentGrowth - settledGrowth 4. Apply fee rate: unsettledGrowth  feeRate / 10000

addFeeExemption(uint256).notice: Adds a fee exemption to exclude this value from node operator fee base. The exemption works by increasing the settled growth, effectively treating the exempted amount as if fees were already paid on it.

confirmation(bytes,bytes32).notice: Returns the confirmation expiry for a given call data and confirmer.

confirmingRoles().notice: The roles that must confirm critical parameter changes in the contract.

constructor.notice: Passes the address of the vault hub up the inheritance chain.

correctSettledGrowth(int256,int256).notice: Manually corrects the settled growth value with dual confirmation. Used to correct fee calculation.

disburseFee().notice: Permissionless function to disburse node operator fees. Fee disbursement steps: 1. Calculate current vault growth from latest report 2. Determine fee amount on unsettled growth 3. Update settled growth to current growth (marking fees as paid) 4. Withdraws fee amount from vault to node operator recipient

feeRate().notice: Node operator fee rate in basis points (1 bp = 0.01%). Cannot exceed 100.00% (10000 basis points).

feeRecipient().notice: Address that receives node operator fee disbursements. This address is set by the node operator manager and receives disbursed fees.

grantRoles((address,bytes32)[]).notice: Mass-grants multiple roles to multiple accounts.

initialized().notice: Indicates whether the contract has been initialized

isApprovedToConnect().notice: Flag indicating whether the vault is approved by the node operator to connect to VaultHub. The node operator's approval is needed to confirm the validity of fee calculations, particularly the settled growth.

latestCorrectionTimestamp().notice: Timestamp of the most recent settled growth correction. This timestamp is used to prevent retroactive fees after a fee rate change. The timestamp ensures that all fee exemptions and corrections are fully reported before changing the fee rate. Regular fee disbursements do not update this timestamp.

latestReport().notice: The latest vault report for the underlying StakingVault.

revokeRoles((address,bytes32)[]).notice: Mass-revokes multiple roles from multiple accounts.

setApprovedToConnect(bool).notice: Approves/forbids connection to VaultHub. Approval implies that the node operator agrees with the current fee parameters, particularly the settled growth used as baseline for fee calculations.

setConfirmExpiry(uint256).notice: Sets the confirmation expiry period with dual confirmation.

setFeeRate(uint256).notice: Updates the node operator's fee rate with dual confirmation.

setFeeRecipient(address).notice: Sets the address that receives node operator fee disbursements.

settledGrowth().notice: Growth of the vault not subject to fees. Growth is the difference between inOutDelta and totalValue, i.e. the component of totalValue that has not been directly funded to the underlying StakingVault via `fund()`:    inOutDelta + growth = totalValue Settled growth is the portion of the total growth that: - has already been charged by the node operator, - or is not subject to fee (exempted) such as unguaranteed/side deposits, consolidations.

stakingVault().notice: Returns the address of the underlying StakingVault.
